{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 03:43:54.472217", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview of Current Health\\n- Data-plane is non-functional. No host-to-host communication succeeds, even between hosts on the same leaf switch and same subnet (10.0.0.0/24).\\n- Control-plane connectivity to the SDN controller’s IP (20.0.0.100) from switches is OK at the IP layer, but OpenFlow control sessions fail.\\n\\nObserved Symptoms and Tests\\n- Host reachability:\\n  - host_1_1 -> host_1_2: ping timed out.\\n  - host_1_1 -> host_2_1: “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.0.0.1 (local host).\\n  - host_2_1 -> host_2_2: “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.0.0.9.\\n  - host_2_1 -> host_1_2: “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.0.0.9.\\n  - Interpretation: L2 switching/bridging is not happening; ARP resolution fails, resulting in local host unreachable responses.\\n- Switch management network:\\n  - leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1 can ping 20.0.0.100 successfully (low-latency, 0% loss). Thus, the management network (20.0.0.0/24) is up.\\n- Open vSwitch controller state:\\n  - All switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) configured with Controller \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\" and fail_mode: secure.\\n  - is_connected: false on all; status shows last_error=\"Connection refused\", state=BACKOFF.\\n  - ovs-ofctl dump-flows on all bridges returns no flow entries.\\n  - ovs-ofctl show indicates all physical ports are LIVE and up; only the LOCAL port is down (expected).\\n- Host and interface status:\\n  - Hosts have correct IPs in 10.0.0.0/24 and link is UP at the interface level.\\n  - Switch access and inter-switch ports report LIVE at the OpenFlow port level.\\n\\nAnomaly Detection\\n- Critical anomaly: The SDN controller at tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 is refusing OpenFlow TCP connections. As a result, all OVS devices are in fail_mode secure without any programmed flows, causing all data-plane traffic to be dropped.\\n- Secondary manifestation: Because there are no flows, ARP requests are not forwarded/handled, leading to “Destination Host Unreachable” even within the same L2 segment on a leaf.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Faulty component: SDN controller service/end-point at 20.0.0.100:6633 (application/service level). The devices attempting to connect (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are operational at the OS and interface level and can reach 20.0.0.100 over IP, but the OpenFlow service does not accept connections.\\n- Affected devices: All OVS bridges—leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1—are impacted due to their secure fail mode and absence of controller connection/flows.\\n- Non-faulty components:\\n  - Physical/virtual links between hosts and leafs, and between leafs and spine, appear up (LIVE).\\n  - Management network is healthy (ICMP to 20.0.0.100 works from all switches).\\n  - Host IP configs and routing within 10.0.0.0/24 are consistent.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- The controller process is not listening/available on TCP port 6633 at 20.0.0.100 (connection refused). With fail_mode secure and zero OpenFlow rules installed, OVS drops all traffic, breaking L2/L3 connectivity across the fabric.\\n\\nKey Evidence\\n- Controller connectivity status (all switches):\\n  - is_connected=false; last_error=\"Connection refused\"; state=BACKOFF; target=\"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\".\\n- Flow tables:\\n  - ovs-ofctl dump-flows leaf_1/leaf_2/spine_1: empty (no entries).\\n- Host pings:\\n  - Intra-leaf and inter-leaf pings: 100% loss; local “Destination Host Unreachable” responses indicate no L2 forwarding/ARP resolution.\\n- Management pings:\\n  - leaf_1/leaf_2/spine_1 -> 20.0.0.100: successful ICMP responses, confirming IP reachability to the controller host.\\n\\nConclusion\\n- The network’s data-plane failure is caused by the SDN controller not accepting OpenFlow connections on 20.0.0.100:6633. All switches, configured in fail_mode=secure with no flows present, are consequently dropping traffic, leading to complete loss of host-to-host connectivity., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='ac5b3fe5-510f-4f38-836a-a22739724e09'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
